# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HWAX Portal — routing destinations.   Format:  <system-id>=<URL>
#
# Set a system's URL here → its tile becomes clickable AND nginx adds /<id>/ → that URL.
# Leave it commented → the tile stays "coming_soon".
# The names/logos/descriptions live in systems.yaml; ONLY the destination is here.
#
# After editing:  ./infra/scripts/restart.sh   (or POST /systems/reload as admin)
#
# ── This file is for PROXY-mode tiles (integration_type: proxy in systems.yaml) ──────────────
# nginx reverse-proxies  <portal>/<id>/  →  the URL below, PASSING the /<id>/ prefix through.
# The URL is resolved by the NGINX HOST (not the user's browser), so:
#   same server as the portal :  heax-hub=http://localhost:4180
#   another server (by IP)    :  heax-hub=http://10.123.45.67:4180
#
# ⚠️ Because the /<id>/ prefix is passed through, the service MUST serve under that base path
#    (e.g. Vite `base: '/<id>/'`, or its own router base) or its absolute /assets/... will 404.
#    A destination WITH a path (…:8001/dashboard/) instead maps /<id>/ → /dashboard/.
#
# Services with their OWN address (own domain / externally-exposed port) do NOT belong here —
# set integration_type: external-url + url in systems.yaml; the tile links to it directly.
#
# Per-env: dev edits this file; prod uses config/routes.prod.env via ROUTES_PATH. Any single
# line can be overridden by an env var:  SYS_HEAX_HUB_URL=http://10.0.0.5:4180
# After editing:  ./infra/scripts/restart.sh   (or POST /systems/reload as admin)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Live on this host (same server as the portal) — proxied under /<id>/.
heax-hub=http://localhost:4180
# AI Data Hub serves UI at /dashboard and /api,/static,/downloads at its root → map /ai-data-hub/
# to the service ROOT (trailing slash strips the prefix). Its FastAPI redirects "/" → dashboard,
# and dashboard.js derives the prefix, so everything resolves under /ai-data-hub/.
ai-data-hub=http://localhost:8001/
mx-white-paper=http://localhost:5173

# report-archive → temporarily external-url (http://hwax.sec.samsung.net:3001) in systems.yaml.
# smart-twin-cluster / spdm have their own domains → external-url in systems.yaml (not here).
